(20468, 'dapsone gel, 5%', 'N/A', 'moderate', '7.4 Concomitant Use with Drugs that Induce Methemoglobinemia Concomitant use of Dapsone Gel, 5% with drugs that induce methemoglobinemia such as sulfonamides, acetaminophen, acetanilide, aniline dyes, benzocaine, chloroquine, dapsone, naphthalene, nitrates and nitrites, nitrofurantoin, nitroglycerin, nitroprusside, pamaquine, para-aminosalicylic acid, phenacetin, phenobarbital, phenytoin, primaquine, and quinine may increase the risk for developing methemoglobinemia [see Warnings and Precautions (5.1)].', 'DailyMed'),
(20468, 'noxivent 102', 'N/A', 'minor', 'DRUG INTERACTIONS 7.1 Nitric Oxide Donor Agents Nitric oxide donor agents such as prilocaine, sodium nitroprusside and nitroglycerine may increase the risk of developing methemoglobinemia.', 'DailyMed'),
(20468, 'nitric oxide', 'N/A', 'minor', '7.1 Nitric Oxide Donor Agents Nitric oxide donor agents such as prilocaine, sodium nitroprusside and nitroglycerine may increase the risk of developing methemoglobinemia.', 'DailyMed'),
(26889, 'labetalol hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'The anesthesiologist should be informed when a patient is receiving labetalol.Labetalol blunts the reflex tachycardia produced by nitroglycerin without preventing its hypotensive effect. If labetalol is used with nitroglycerin in patients with angina pectoris, additional antihypertensive effects may occur.Care should be taken if labetalol is used concomitantly with calcium channel antagonists of the verapamil type.', 'DailyMed'),
(26889, 'nitroglycerin', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Nitroglycerin acts directly on vascular muscle. Marked symptomatic orthostatic hypotension has been reported when calcium channel blockers and oral controlled-release nitroglycerin were used in combination.', 'DailyMed'),
(26889, 'amlodipine besylate', 'N/A', 'major', 'Effect of amlodipine on other agents ATORVASTATIN: Coadministration of multiple 10 mg doses of amlodipine with 80 mg of atorvastatin resulted in no significant change in the steady state pharmacokinetic parameters of atorvastatin.DIGOXIN: Coadministration of amlodipine with digoxin did not change serum digoxin levels or digoxin renal clearance in normal volunteers.ETHANOL (alcohol): Single and multiple 10 mg doses of amlodipine had no significant effect on the pharmacokinetics of ethanol.WARFARIN: Coadministration of amlodipine with warfarin did not change the warfarin prothrombin response time.In clinical trials, amlodipine has been safely administered with thiazide diuretics, beta-blockers, angiotensin-converting enzyme inhibitors, long-acting nitrates, sublingual nitroglycerin, digoxin,', 'DailyMed'),
(26889, 'lisinopril', 'N/A', 'minor', 'This included post myocardial infarction patients who were receiving intravenous or transdermal nitroglycerin.', 'DailyMed'),
(26889, 'captopril', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Agents Having Vasodilator Activity Data on the effect of concomitant use of vasodilators in patients receiving captopril for heart failure are not available; therefore, nitroglycerin or other nitrates (as used for management of angina) or other drugs having vasodilator activity should, if possible, be discontinued before starting captopril.', 'DailyMed'),
(26889, 'amlobenz', 'N/A', 'minor', 'In clinical trials, amlodipine has been safely administered with thiazide diuretics, beta-blockers, ACE inhibitors, long-acting nitrates, sublingual nitroglycerin, digoxin, warfarin, nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs, antibiotics, and oral hypoglycemic drugs.', 'DailyMed'),
(26889, 'nitroglycerin sustained-release capsules', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug Interactions The vasodilating effects of nitroglycerin may be additive with those of other vasodilators.', 'DailyMed'),
(26889, 'amlodipine besylate, arginine', 'N/A', 'minor', 'In clinical trials, amlodipine besylate has been safely administered with thiazide diuretics, betablockers,angiotensin-converting enzyme inhibitors, long-acting nitrates, sublingual nitroglycerin,digoxin, warfarin, non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs, antibiotics, and oral hypoglycemic drugs.', 'DailyMed'),
(26889, 'lisinopril, arginine', 'N/A', 'minor', 'This included post myocardial infarction patients who were receiving intravenous or transdermal nitroglycerin.', 'DailyMed'),
